Core scripts available from `package.json`:

| Script | Command | Classification |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `check` | `npm run check --workspaces --if-present` | Pre-RC validation |
| `test` | TypeScript compilation into `.tmp-tests/*` plus `node --test tooling/tests/*.test.mjs` | Pre-RC validation; generates temporary artifacts |
| `conformance` | TypeScript compile of conformance package plus `node tooling/conformance/run-conformance.mjs` | Pre-RC validation; generates temporary artifacts |

Recommended minimum Core validation sequence for a dedicated Core validation sprint:

1. `npm run check --workspaces --if-present`
2. `npm test`
3. `npm run conformance`
4. Recheck `git status --short --branch` and remove only known temporary artifacts if explicitly authorized by the sprint plan.

These validations were not executed in this request to preserve the "do not alter Core code" and "do not touch generated artifacts" restrictions. Core tests are expected to create `.tmp-tests` or `.tmp-conformance` directories.

